commentary: Bumrah to Finch, no run length ball, has jagged back in at 141.8kph, and rapped him on the pads. Loud appeal, and they finally review it after it was turned down initially. The front foot is fine, gets back in appreciably, and also misses the bat. Finch was high up off the ground as he looked to defend, so height could be the only question. And it is! Goes over the stumps, and so India lose their review early!

commentary: Kuldeep Yadav to Finch, OUT appeal for lbw, and given! Finch falls for 93? Well, we need to wait. He's reviewing. Length ball on leg, and the ball straightens after pitching. Ball crashing into middle and leg stump, and the India supporters finally find their voice

commentary: Cummins to Sharma, OUT appeal for lbw, but the umpire doesn't give it! Australia are surely reviewing. This was a length ball that didn't rise as much, and Rohit was surprised by the (lack of) bounce. Ball angles in, and hits him on the back leg, so that's worrying for India. Was there any inside edge? There's a bit of a spike, but is that ball grazing the front-pad or bat? Umpire thinks that's grazed the front-pad and ball-tracking says that the ball is crashing into middle stump! A good review, and India lose their second opener too

commentary: Zampa to Kohli, 2 runs full on off, and he muscles a straight drive down to long on. First, Shaun Marsh at long on dives to save the boundary, but the ball is rolling towards the rope, and therefore Pat Cummins, from long off, comes to retrieve the ball. Cummins parries the ball back from just inside the boundary, so Australia save two runs. Commitment at it's best!
